    <briefdescription>
<para>empirical-distribution risk measures </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This class wraps a somewhat generic statistic tool and adds a number of risk measures (e.g.: value-at-risk, expected shortfall, etc.) based on the data distribution as reported by the underlying statistic tool.</para>
